message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for generating clarification questions, which are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it deals with natural language processing. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) are also likely categories as they deal with machine learning techniques. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper deals with generating questions to elicit new information. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category, but still relevant as the paper uses a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) for generating questions.
